pub unsafe fn rts_set(p: &mut Proc, flag: u32) {
    let was_runnable = p.rts_flags.load(Ordering::Relaxed) == 0;
    p.rts_flags.fetch_or(flag, Ordering::Relaxed);
    let nr = p.nr;
    if was_runnable {
        // SAFETY: caller's invariants; `p`'s borrow has been captured.
        unsafe { dequeue(nr) }
    }
}
```
- Sets bits in `rts_flags` atomically
- If process was runnable (all bits clear), dequeues it
- **NLL pattern:** captures `nr` from `p`, borrow ends, then calls `dequeue`

**rts_unset** (lines 200-208) — Full quoted text:
